&gt; How would this.el? this be translated into a hook component?

Use [useRef](https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-reference.html#useref) hook.

&gt; 2) How does the div translate into a hook?

Simply return `div` using `el` ref.

```
function Scene() {
  const el = useRef(null);

  return &lt;div ref={el} /&gt; // init el ref
}
```

Alternatively, you may also use a [callback ref](https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-faq.html#how-can-i-measure-a-dom-node) for purpose of *measuring the node dimensions*.

```
function Scene() {
  const [rect, setRect] = useState(null);

  const callbackRef = useCallback(node =&gt; {
    if (node !== null) {
      setRect(node.getBoundingClientRect());
    }
  }, []);

  return &lt;div ref={callbackRef} /&gt; // use callback ref
}
```

